x4freetext: TIME OF FLIGHT, FLIGHT PATHS = 31.17 M FOR
SCATTERING AND TRANSMISSION, 60.6 M FOR CAPTURE
EXPERIMENT. TOF RESOLUTION DE(FWHM)/E IS 2.E-3 FOR
SCATTERING, 0.7 TO 6.7 NS/M FOR CAPTURE  AND 1.5 TO
SIX SCINTILLATORS (LND TYPE 800, PRESSURE 250 ATM) FOR
.MONTE-CARLO PROGRAM TO THE CORRECTIONS OF SCATTERING
.CAPTURE AREAS WERE ANALYZED WITH A PROGRAM BY FROEHNER
.TRANSMISSION DATA WERE ANALYZED WITH A MODIFIED ATTA-
HARVEY AREA PROGRAM BY KOLAR, EUR-4760E (1972).
SECTION, USING A VALUE OF 11.28 +- 0.6 BARN.
ASSUMING THAT THIS CROSS SECTION VARIES AS
1/SQRT(E). THE ABSOLUTE CALIBRATION OF THE PRODUCT
DETECTOR EFFICIENCY TIMES NEUTRON FLUX WAS DONE BY
OBSERVING CAPTURE IN BLACK RESONANCES IN AG.
.ARE RESPECTIVELY NEUTRON YIELD, AREA AND TRANSMISSION.
